pull_request.title: KAT testing using hashes
pull_request.body:
As discussed on the developer mailing list, this is to remove the need to keep 37MB of KATs in the repo.

The most relevant changes are in `tests/test_kat.py`. The rest is just deletion of full KAT files and addition of .sha256 files (via `scripts/genkatsha256.sh`).

Tests [ran OK here](https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/baentsch/liboqs/302/workflows/9e4c1d54-1b89-4374-8391-1731ca00cc19)

pull_request.title: Added invalid ciphertext test in test_kem
pull_request.body:
Test now generates a random ciphertext and expect an invalid decapsulation or non-matching shared secret. Also replaced invalid signature with random array vs one with only the first byte modified (to potentially catch more errors).

- [ ] Fix SIKE compressed decapsulation error on bad data before merging this
